[4.2]
Structure of a DNA ï‚· Chromosomes are made of a molecule called DNA ï‚· Each chromosome is a very long molecule of tightly coiled DNA 
ï‚· Two strands coiled together to form a double helix ï‚· Each strand contains chemicals called bases ï‚· Cross-links between strands are formed by pairs of bases ï‚· The bases always pair up in the same way:  o A and T o C and G 

