Chlorophyll Is Necessary for Photosynthesis ï‚· Take a potted plant with variegated (green and white) leaves. ï‚· Destarch the plant by keeping it in complete darkness for about 48 hours. ï‚· Expose the plant to the sunlight for a few days. ï‚· Leaf boiled in water for 2 minutes to break down cell walls, denature enzymes and allow for easier penetration by ethanol. 
ï‚· Warmed in ethanol until leaf is colourless to extract chlorophyll, which would mask observation  ï‚· Dipped in water briefly: to soften leaf ï‚· Leaf is placed on a white tile and iodine is added. If starch is present, colour will be blue-black and if absent, it will remain orange 
 
