Limiting Factors â€¢Limiting factor: something present in the environment in such short supply that it restricts life processes. 
Light intensity ï‚· As the amount of light increases, the rate of photosynthesis increases (a-b) ï‚· The limiting factor is light  ï‚· Increasing the amount of light after a certain point has no effect on the rate (c) ï‚· The limiting factor is now carbon dioxide or temperature  
 Carbon dioxide concentration ï‚· As the amount of carbon dioxide increases, the rate of photosynthesis increases (a-b) ï‚· The limiting factor is carbon dioxide  ï‚· Increasing amount of carbon dioxide after a certain point has not effect on rate (c)  ï‚· The limiting factor is now light or temperature (warmth) 
 Temperature ï‚· As temperature increases, the rate of photosynthesis increases until it reaches optimum temperature 40Â°c (a) ï‚· The limiting factor is the temperature  ï‚· Increasing the temperature above 40Â°c will cause the enzymes to denature (b)  ï‚· This will decrease rate of photosynthesis  
