 Glasshouse Systems To increase the crop yield, farmers control the limiting factors: ï‚· CO2 enrichment: paraffin is burnt to increase CO2 concentration by three times the original amount and doubling the yield ï‚· Optimum temperature: thermostatically controlled heaters make the temperature right for enzymes to work ï‚· Optimum light: light has a high intensity for more photosynthesis, the correct wavelengths (red and blue not green) and duration controls production of fruit 
