[7.2]
Effects of Malnutrition ï‚· Starvation: losing strength & finally dying because of lack of food ï‚· Coronary heart disease: eating too much fats which are rich in saturated fatty acids and cholesterol, may lead to heart attack ï‚· Constipation: lack of roughages in food causes constipation because roughages are indigestible and form bulks. Friction between bulks and walls of intestine stimulate the peristalsis ï‚· Obesity: Eating too much fats and carbohydrates leads to their storage in storage in the body mainly in the forms of fats and causing an increase in body weight. This can cause; heart attack, stroke, joint pain, mobility impairment, high blood pressure {#
