[8.7]
Translocation ï‚· Movement of sucrose and amino acids in phloem; from regions of production (sources) to regions of storage or to regions of utilization in respiration or growth (sinks). ï‚· Translocation in different seasons: o Spring: sucrose transported from stores in roots to leaves o Summer & early autumn: sucrose goes from photosynthesizing leaves to root stores, 
