Lymphatic System ï‚· Circulation of body fluids, and the production of lymphocytes.  ï‚· Lymph node contains many lymphocytes which filter lymph.  ï‚· Tissue fluid: made when plasma is squeezed out of capillaries.  ï‚· Substances diffuse between cells and tissue fluid.  ï‚· Lymph vessels collect lymph and return it to the blood.  ï‚· Tissue fluid returns to the capillaries by osmosis. {#
[9.8]
Blood ï‚· Red blood cells: haemoglobin and oxygen transport ï‚· White blood cells: phagocytosis and antibody formation ï‚· Platelets: causing clotting ï‚· Plasma: transport of blood cells, ions, soluble nutrients, hormones, carbon dioxide, urea and plasma proteins 
  
