Immune system  PHAGOCYTE LYMPHOCYTE ï‚· Phagocyte has lobed nucleus and vesicles containing digestive enzymes.  ï‚· Phagocytosis: engulf pathogen, vesicles fuse with vacuole, enzymes digest bacteria.  ï‚· Antigen: protein/ carbohydrate on surface of pathogen which provokes immune system ï‚· Lymphocytes are found in blood and in lymph nodes  ï‚· Large nucleus and they produce antibodies,  ï‚· Antibodies: Y-shaped protein, bind to label pathogens.  ï‚· Then either destroyed by being ingested by phagocytes, or the antibodies may do it. {#
[9.1]
 Blood Clotting ï‚· Reduces blood loss and keeps pathogens out ï‚· Fibrinogen (inactive) turns to fibrin (activated), and forms a mesh to trap red blood cells, which eventually dries to form a scab. 